# Step 6
Let's address the height issue to start off with.

The default height of the widget is 350 pixels, you can easily override this by setting the defaultHeight on $scope.
For now we'll set this to 382 pixels.

__`appController.js`__

```js
$scope.defaultHeight = 382;
```

Next we can add some more data to the events, such as the sports, countries and leagues.
This information is all in the path property of the event, so in our iteration we'll add this below our competitors
We simply iterate over the path property and output the name of each path object. Let's also separate the path names with a slash (/).

__`index.html`__
```html
<div class="l-flexbox">
   <div class="l-flexbox" ng-repeat="p in liveEvent.event.path"
        style="max-width: {{ 100 / liveEvent.event.path.length }}%">
      <span class="l-flexbox l-flex-3">
         <span class="text-truncate">{{p.name}}</span>
      </span>
      <span ng-if="!$last" class="l-pl-5 l-pr-5">{{!$last?'/':''}}</span>
   </div>
</div>
```

There are some classes to set some styling on these new elements as well.
- kw-event-path: the container element for paths
- kw-event-path-name: a path element
- kw-event-path-divider: a divider element for our path names

__`index.html`__
```html
<div class="kw-event-path l-flexbox">
   <div class="l-flexbox" ng-repeat="p in liveEvent.event.path"
        style="max-width: {{ 100 / liveEvent.event.path.length }}%">
      <span class="kw-event-path-name l-flexbox l-flex-3">
         <span class="text-truncate">{{p.name}}</span>
      </span>
      <span ng-if="!$last" class="kw-event-path-divider l-pl-5 l-pr-5">{{!$last?'/':''}}</span>
   </div>
</div>
```
